      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OLE MISS (2) was comfortably accounted for in much stronger over 1500m at Hawkesbury. That followed a 4.6L Maiden win over 1400m at this track at the previous outing. Has the blinkers on for the first time and the ability to return to the winner's list. MEDDLESOME (7) races forward and brings strong sprinting form. Draws low, and Looker replaces the apprentice. Has her first crack at 1600m and is likely to make a good fist of it. DIPIERDOMENICO (1) comes back to 1600m in an easier race and prior to last time had been threatening another win. Has a handy 3kg claim today and rates to make the finish. BIG SHORT (3) finished it off okay this trip at Moree off a plainer run. He's consistently within range and maps well. Won his only start at the track over this distance. ARRABBIATA (5) dropped right out at Moree, well supported, but just missed here over 1400m prior from the speed. That effort would see him very competitive.",
